<HEADLINE>
TROJANS PLAN FOR GEORGES
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SCOTT WOLF  
 c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   TALLAHASSEE, Fla. _ USC's game with Florida State was on as of
Thursday evening, but Trojans athletic department officials were
drawing up contingency plans in case Hurricane Georges forced
postponement of the Saturday contest.
</P>
<P>
   USC is planning to leave for Atlanta or Jacksonville by bus
Saturday morning in the event the game is canceled and flights are
unable to get out of Tallahassee.
</P>
<P>
   Hurricane Georges was forecast to travel through Southern
Florida and toward the Gulf of Mexico, although it is also expected
to travel through the Florida panhandle and could hit Tallahassee,
which is in the northern part of the state.
</P>
<P>
   Florida State was scheduled to be begin issuing hurricane
updates this morning but had not mentioned any plans concerning the
football game.
</P>
<P>
   The latest weather report forecast rain and a high of 79 degrees
for Saturday.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-09-25-98 0038EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
