<P>
   ROSENFELD-SHORTTAKES _ I said I wouldn't watch it. But I did, at
least about an hour of Bill Clinton's grand jury performance. I
thought it was pretty dull, which, I'd guess, is what the president
was shooting for. His strong suit was his supposed unwillingness to
kiss and tell. They say a gentleman doesn't. (Rosenfeld, Cox News
Service) MOVED THURSDAY.
</P>
<P>
   GLASS-COLUMN _ Many Americans appear ready to give the brush-off
to the relentless independent counsel. When it comes to Clinton,
they may see some troubling ``misdemeanors,'' but no genuine ``high
crimes'' that would justify his ouster. Why? (Glass, Cox News
Service) MOVED 9/24.
</P>
<P>
   TEEPEN-COLUMN _ Tom Teepen is on vacation. His column will
resume next week. (Teepen, Cox News Service)
</P>
