   BUILDING-WASTE _ WASHINGTON _ But for a $250 shower curtain, the
$1.3 billion federal building project might have quietly cleared
its final obstacles and into construction phase. And that bump in
the road was a major annoyance for Sen. John Warner, R-Va., who for
years has been shepherding plans for the new U.S. Patent and
Trademark Office, proposed for his state. With a contract on the
verge of being awarded, citizens watchdog groups discovered the
offending shower curtain among hundreds of other extravagant items
on a list of $64 million in furnishings for the new complex.
(Malone, Cox News Service 720).
</P>
