COMPUTER-MUSIC (Los Angeles _ The Internet is transforming the
music business in a variety of ways, allowing fans to find each
other, no-name bands to find an audience, pirates to find customers
and music lovers to find the exact songs they love for their own
greatest hits packages. A list of what is available is included. By
David Bloom. 
. 
FANTASY-TV (Los Angeles) _ This is the darker, more sinister
Malcolm McDowell-as-Mr.-Roarke remake of the '70s hit ``Fantasy
Island.'' And the show wastes no time establishing the differences
between the two versions. Roarke rummages through his closet, which
has an endless supply of identical white suits. He eventually
settles on the one black ensemble in the lot. By Keith Marder. 
. 
