<P>
   THOMPSON-COLUMN (Washington) _ Out of the furor over sex, sin
and semantics that has debased the White House and besmirched Bill
Clinton's presidency, an unprecedented dichotomy of opinion has
emerged, built around a single basic question: What is important to
Americans? By ROBERT E. THOMPSON. (Filed Wednesday)
</P>
