(EDS: Accompanies CARS-WILLIAMS-COLUMN) 
(For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
c.1998 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   At A Glance:
</P>
<P>
   1999 Ford F-250 Super Duty Crew Cab pickup
</P>
<P>
   The Package: Full-size, heavy-duty (11,200-pound gross weight),
four-door, six-passenger, rear-drive pickup truck, a completely
redesigned model for 1999.
</P>
<P>
   Highlights: Three engine choices available _ a V-8 and V-10
gasoline and a high-torque V-8 turbodiesel (which came in our test
truck); roomy and comfortable cab; rounder, more aerodynamic
styling; carlike interior with leather seats; excellent ride and
road handling; a reputation as a tough, dependable work truck;
outstanding trailer-towing capabilities.
</P>
<P>
   Negatives: Pricey with all the trimmings.
</P>
<P>
   Major competitors: Chevrolet/GMC heavy-duty pickups, which are
due for a redesign next year.
</P>
<P>
   EPA fuel economy: No EPA ratings are required for vehicles in
this size class; manufacturer declined to provide estimated
mileage.
</P>
<P>
   Base price: $25,030 plus $640 transportation.
</P>
<P>
   Price as tested: $34,195, including transportation.
</P>
<P>
   On The Road rating: A-plus.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com) &QL;
