A4982 &Cx1f; tad-z
u w &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-RIDERS-DATA26-COX     09-25 0436
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-RIDERS-DATA26-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    With RIDERS
 &HT;    c.1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Here are some environmental amendments to various fiscal 1999
appropriations bills, and what they would do:
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Mining company environmental rules: Postpone the department's
efforts to write new environmental standards for hard-rock mining
operations on government lands.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Commercial fishing in Glacier Bay National Park: Block
National Park Service efforts to phase out commercial fishing in
Glacier Bay, Alaska, where it has been going on for decades despite
a federal law against it.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Izembek road: Allow construction of a $30 million road through
Alaska's Izembek National Wildlife Refuge and waive all applicable
environmental laws.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Oil industry royalties: Block increases in the royalties that
oil companies pay for oil taken from government lands.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Rent subsidies in national forest: Block efforts by the U.S.
Forest Service to increase rent paid on vacation cottages in
Idaho's Sawtooth National Forest.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Tongass National Forest timber sale: Require the Forest
Service to sell 241 million board feet of timber at subsidized
prices.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Grizzly bears in Idaho and Montana: Prohibit the Fish and
Wildlife Service from reintroducing grizzly bears into the
Selway-Bitterroot ecosystem in Idaho and Montana.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Land Between the Lakes: transfer jurisdiction for 17,000 acres
of hardwood forest in Tennessee and Kentucky from the Tennessee
Valley Authority to the Forest Service, with incentives to log and
develop it.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Chugach Forest road: grant a road construction easement
through the 700,000-acre Cooper River Delta in Alaska's Chugach
National Forest.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Develop Florida coastal barrier tracts: Remove several Florida
land parcels from the Coastal Barriers System, making the areas
eligible for federal flood insurance.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Kyoto Protocol: Ban use of federal funds to implement U.S.
participation in the Kyoto Protocol to limit ``greenhouse'' gases
believed to contribute to global warming.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  PCB Cleanup: Place a moratorium on use of dredging to clean up
toxic PCB pollutants in the Hudson and Housatonic Rivers in New
York and Massachusetts.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Mercury from power plants: Delay EPA regulations that would
limit the levels of toxic mercury that electric companies are
allowed to release into the air from power plants.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Global Warming: prohibit use of U.S. funds to encourage
``developing countries'' to participate in greenhouse gas reduction
under the Kyoto Accord.
</P>
<P>
   ENDIT
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
