<HEADLINE>
ACCESSORIZING THE FAMILY PET
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By BARBARA DE WITT 
c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ &UR;  &LR; Everybody knows dogs are man's best friend. Look
at Buddy. You don't hear him ratting on the president.
</P>
<P>
   For such loyal canine companions, Coach now makes snazzy dog
collars and leashes to complement pet owners' purses and
briefcases. The collars, $38, and leashes, $48, are made of braided
leather in natural tan or black and are available exclusively at
the Coach store in the Century City Shopping Center, 10250 Santa
Monica Blvd. (310) 282-0772. And, since celebrity spokesmodels are
trendy, Coach has hired Moose, the Jack Russell terrier who plays
Eddie on TV's ``Frasier,'' for its advertising campaign.
</P>
<P>
   Other new ideas for pet owners come from Hammacher Schlemmer,
309 N. Rodeo Drive, Beverly Hills. (310) 859-7255. They've got a
cool Dutch wicker basket for $34.95 that attaches to the front of
your bicycle, featuring an open-weave iron wire cover to keep
little Daisy from leaping out of the basket while you're pedaling
down the street. Also available is a self-cleaning litter box for
cats with a microprocessor-controlled system that automatically
cleans up after your cat. Miz Hot Tips hasn't tried it, but it
sounds like a dream come true and is priced at $179.95.
</P>
<P>
   For more products, check out the new Double Dog Dare Ya grooming
and doggie day-care center at 2703 W. Burbank Blvd., Burbank. They
offer toys, treats, training videos and also have a cat spa with a
Tahitian jungle theme that includes a bubbling waterfall. The
number is (818) 846-2234.
</P>
<P>
   CITY OF LIGHT: You'll always remember Paris when you flick the
switch on the Eiffel Tower lamp Miz Hot Tips found at Target
stores. The lamp base is a wire design that really resembles the
French landmark and is priced at $29.99. You can top it with your
own shade, or try theirs with silver trim for $12.99.
</P>
<P>
   CHEAP CHIC: You've seen those famous Gucci loafers with the
silver trim across the toe ... and the prices. If you're like Miz
Hot Tips and only want the look, try the new collection of suede
loafers by Apostrophe in gray, purple, green, brown and black at
Sears. They're only $17.99 a pair.
</P>
<P>
   WRITING STYLE: Handwritten letters seem sooo romantic in this
e-mail era, especially when written with an elegant fountain pen.
For inspiration, take a gander at the new exhibit presented by
Cartier, ``The Art of Ecriture: An Historical Collection of Vintage
Writing Instruments'' on display through Wednesday at Signatore in
the Century City Shopping Center. Hours are 10 a.m. to 9 p.m.
weekdays, 10 a.m. to 6 p.m. Saturday, 11 a.m. to 6 p.m. Sunday.
Call (310) 553-8830 for information.
</P>
<P>
   FASHION PARADE: Looking for a fashionable event to attend? The
Women's Odyssey Organization in Canoga Park is holding its 18th
annual fashion shown and luncheon at 11:30 a.m. Sunday at the
Warner Center Marriott, 21850 Oxnard St., in Woodland Hills.
Tickets are $35 and proceeds benefit the group's alcohol recovery
house. The number to call is (818) 998-8972.
</P>
<P>
   ON MALL PATROL: So, you've been so busy watching the Starr
report on TV that you have no idea what's going on at the local
mall?
</P>
<P>
   The annual Liz Claiborne Charity Shopping Day is slated for
Thursday at two local malls, Topanga Plaza in Canoga Park and the
Glendale Galleria. It's an opportunity to shop at the Liz Claiborne
store, which will donate 10 percent of the day's sales to the
Glendale YWCA Shelter and Haven Hills domestic-violence shelter.
The stores lso are offering ``Love is not abuse'' watches for $20.
The only number on the dial is 12, to signify that every 12 seconds
a woman is abused in this country.
</P>
<P>
   Topanga Plaza will also host a traveling photo exhibit called
``Diana, a Lasting Tribute'' Oct. 10 to 21. There's no admission
fee, but there is a contribution box for the Princess of Wales
Memorial Fund.
</P>
<P>
   Over in Ventura County at The Oaks mall, 222 W. Hillcrest Drive,
Thousand Oaks, there's a lot of renovation going on again. This
time it's the addition of a circular drive to serve drop-off and
handicapped passengers and also a valet parking station. Its newest
store is KB Toys (the same company formerly known as Kay-Bee Toys),
but more stores should be open for holiday shopping.
</P>
<P>
   And in Beverly Hills, the Neiman Marcus store at 9700 Wilshire
Blvd. has opened a David Linley accessory shop. Linley is the son
of Princess Margaret and a respected furniture designer. The royal
designer will be at the store to greet customers at 2 p.m. Oct. 23
in the Galleries department.
</P>
</TEXT>
