<P>
   DISEASE-RESEARCH _ WASHINGTON _ As cancer survivors participated
this weekend in ``the March,'' a nationwide demonstration against
the disease, organizers of the affair had their eyes on more than
$14 billion the government spends each year on medical research.
Many cancer survivors feel that given the number of lives it takes,
the disease does not get a fair share of federal research funds
distributed by the National Institutes of Health (NIH), said Ellen
Stovall, president of the March. (Nesmith, Cox News Service 780).
</P>
