   TEACHERS _ WASHINGTON _ The American Federation of Teachers and
the National Education Association hold a conference to express
their concerns that school systems are coping with teacher
shortages by compromising on teacher quality. Education Secretary
Richard Riley is among the speakers. (Monroe, Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   RIDERS _ WASHINGTON _ In what has become an annual congressional
struggle, Democrats and Republicans, environmentalists and
regulated interests are going down to the wire over ``riders'' that
have been attached to the Interior Department's appropriation for
next year. These amendments would weaken or at least change various
existing environmental laws. Environmental groups hate them and
President Clinton has promised to veto them, with support among
most congressional Democrats and a few Republicans. With fiscal
1999 beginning Thursday, a Clinton veto over environmental riders
could end up shutting down the government, or much of it. (Nesmith,
Cox News Service 750).
