ASU COACH-SALARY (Flagstaff, Ariz.) - Forget the 1-2 record, the
great expectations for this year's Arizona State University
football team. Head coach Bruce Snyder, already the highest paid
state employee in Arizona, got another raise Friday, pushing his
salary to a minimum of $595,000 with incentives that could make him
as much as $80,000 more. It's tempting to say that football coaches
are paid like CEOs, but the CEO of Arizona State, President Lattie
Coor, makes only about half as much as Snyder. By MARTIN VAN DER
