<P>
   &QL; 
LEIBOWITZ-COLUMN (Phoenix) - His birthday passed yesterday. The
brown-haired boy from Arizona would have turned seven. Imagine with
me gifts, games, a cake, seven candles plus one for good luck _ the
celebration that should have been. Instead, the day vanished like
the birthday boy himself, unnoticed, traceless. Like a sip of air
pushed from pursed lips. The leads in his case, the case of Omar
Vargas, evaporate in that same way. By DAVID LEIBOWITZ. Story moved
in the ``K'' category. &QL; 
