</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    ACC CAPSULES
 &HT;    By Wendy Parker
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   WAKE FOREST VS. CLEMSON
</P>
<P>
   -- When, where: Today, noon, Memorial Stadium, Clemson, S.C.
</P>
<P>
   -- Series: Clemson leads 49-13-1.
</P>
<P>
   -- Records: Wake Forest 1-1, 0-0 ACC; Clemson 1-2, 0-1 ACC.
</P>
<P>
   -- Game notes: The Deacons open their ACC schedule against
Clemson, an opponent they have beaten just once since 1961. ... The
Tigers, who came back against Virginia last week only to fall 20-18
in the final seconds, have allowed opponents to score 51 points in
the first half and just six in the second half of games. ... Wake
quarterback Brian Kuklick is fully healthy for the first time this
season. ... Clemson defensive back Antwan Edwards returned a
kickoff 85 yards and scooped up a fumble and returned it 93 yards
for a touchdown against Virginia.
</P>
<P>
   VIRGINIA VS. DUKE
</P>
<P>
   -- When, where: Today, noon, Wallace Wade Stadium, Durham, N.C.
</P>
<P>
   -- Series: Duke leads 26-23.
</P>
<P>
   -- Records: Virginia 3-0, 1-0 ACC; Duke 2-1, 0-1 ACC.
</P>
<P>
   -- Game notes: The Cavaliers escaped with a 20-18 win over
Clemson last week, their second-straight lackluster performance
after an opening win at Auburn. ... Duke was burned by Florida
State last week, as 35 players suffered from a mysterious flu-like
virus. ... Virginia has won three of its last four games at Wallace
Wade. ... The Blue Devils have lost eight in a row at home to ACC
opponents.
</P>
<P>
   USC VS. FLORIDA STATE
</P>
<P>
   -- When, where: Today, 3:30 p.m., Doak Campbell Stadium,
Tallahassee, Fla.
</P>
<P>
   -- Series: Florida State leads 1-0.
</P>
<P>
   -- Records: Southern Cal 3-0; Florida State 2-1.
</P>
<P>
   -- Game notes: This is one of the best intersectional contests
in the country this week. ... The Seminoles won last year's game
14-7 in Los Angeles. ... The Trojans have gotten off to a good
start under first-year coach Paul Hackett. ... Florida State moved
back into the Top 10 after dropping out for a week after losing to
N.C. State. ... Since joining the ACC, the Seminoles are 10-6-1
against ranked non-conference teams.
</P>
<P>
   TEMPLE VS. MARYLAND
</P>
<P>
   -- When, where: Today, 6 p.m., Byrd Stadium, College Park, Md.
</P>
<P>
   -- Series: Maryland leads 1-0.
</P>
<P>
   -- Records: Temple 0-3; Maryland 1-2.
</P>
<P>
   -- Game notes: The Terrapins return home to play Temple, which
they beat 24-21 last season to give Ron Vanderlinden his first
victory at Maryland. ... Freshman quarterback Randall Jones came
off the bench last week at West Virginia to guide Maryland onthree
second-half scoring drives. ... Terps linebacker Eric Barton has
recorded 14 tackles each against Virginia and West Virginia. ...
Temple is 1-3 against ACC teams.
</P>
