 &HT;    SEC CAPSULES
 &HT;    By Leo Willingham
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   SOUTH CAROLINA VS. MISS. STATE
</P>
<P>
   -- When, where: Today, 12:30 p.m., Williams-Brice Stadium,
Columbia, S.C.
</P>
<P>
   -- Series: Mississippi State leads 4-2.
</P>
<P>
   -- Records: South Carolina 1-2, 0-1 SEC East; Mississippi State
2-1, 1-0 SEC West.
</P>
<P>
   -- Game notes: Mississippi State has won the last two games in
the series (14-10 in Columbia in 1996 and 37-17 in Starkville last
season. ... South Carolina, which has lost its last two home games,
last dropped three in a row at home in 1995, to Tennessee, Florida
and Clemson. . . . Mississippi State coach Jackie Sherrill plans to
wait until just before kickoff to decide whether junior starter
Matt Wyatt or redshirt freshman Wayne Madkin will start at
quarterback.
</P>
