<SLUG> BC-WOMEN-POLICY-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    SIGNING POLICIES
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   WNBA
</P>
<P>
   To sign a contract, a player must meet one of the following
criteria:
</P>
<P>
   -- Reached the age of 22.
</P>
<P>
   -- Completed her college eligibility.
</P>
<P>
   -- Graduated from a four-year college.
</P>
<P>
   -- Played at least two seasons for another professional
basketball league.
</P>
<P>
   Val Ackerman, commissioner: ``We want players who have a certain
maturity _ not only in terms of personal development, but
basketball ability.''
</P>
<P>
   ABL
</P>
<P>
   No defined policy, only the philosophy that it would like
players to finish their college education.
</P>
<P>
   Gary Cavilli, co-founder and CEO: ``If a great player decides to
turn pro, then obviously we'll consider that and listen. Our
highest salary is $150,000, and that's a long way from Michael
Jordan.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
