u a &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-HURRICANE-HELP-NYT &LR;      09-25 0135
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-HURRICANE-HELP-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
HOW TO AID VICTIMS OF THE HURRICANE 
</HEADLINE>
   (With HURRICANE-GEORGES)  
(lb) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   The American Red Cross is accepting financial donations to help
victims of Hurricane Georges. Cash, checks or money orders should
be made out to the American Red Cross Disaster Relief Fund. The
address is American Red Cross, P.O. Box 37243, Washington D.C.
20013.
</P>
<P>
   The Red Cross is also accepting credit-card donations on its
secured Web site: www.redcross.org.
</P>
<P>
   If the money is intended for a particular geographical area,
please specify it. The organization is accepting financial
donations only and will not take contributions of food or clothing.
</P>
<P>
   For more information, call (800) HELPNOW. For information in
Spanish, call (800) 257-7575.
</P>
