<P>
   &UR; BILL'S WORLD &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; By Bill Tammeus, The Kansas City Star &LR;
</P>
<P>
   Mr. Clinton says he hasn't quit fighting for a minimum wage
hike. No surprise from a man who may be out of a job before long.
</P>
<P>
   The man at the next desk says talking about this Clinton mess
with his family has been embarrassing _ especially everything his
teen-agers have had to explain to him.
</P>
<P>
   The Clintons' legal bills for the whole Whitewater-to-Lewinsky
case now total some $8 million, reports say. See how much he's done
for the economy?
</P>
<P>
   Some members of Congress are seeking a way to punish the
president short of impeachment. Is there a Liars Anonymous with a
12-step program?
</P>
<P>
   ``What are we to do with this treasured moment of prosperity and
progress?'' Mr. Clinton asks. Why, spend it watching his grand jury
testimony, what else?
</P>
<P>
   ``The United States has no more important relationship in the
world than our relationship with Japan,'' Mr. Clinton says. Maybe,
but our relationship with ourself right now seems shaky.
</P>
<P>
   Gasoline prices are at a six-year low, reports say. We'll be
more impressed when they're at a 6 9/10-year low.
</P>
<P>
   Teachers in part of Russia are being paid in vodka instead of
cash, it's reported. So? It's still liquid assets.
</P>
<P>
   Automakers, it's reported, are competing in a price war. And the
three-car owner at the next desk wants to know where to go to
surrender.
</P>
<P>
   The new Miss America, Nicole Johnson, has a journalism degree.
But other than that she seems like a decent human being.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
