   With Graphic.
</P>
<P>
   VIATICAL-INSURANCE (Undated) _ Could life insurance get a new
lease on life from a morbid bit of dealmaking that sprang up a
decade ago, when an AIDS diagnosis was a virtual death sentence?
Maybe so, if this year's dramatic growth in the business of buying
up policies from healthy people proves to be the start of a trend.
Viatical settlements, as the arrangments are known, are slowly
filtering into the insurance industry mainstream. By Joseph B.
Treaster. (Moved).
