<P>
   (NYT6) WASHINGTON -- Sept. 25, 1998 -- ADV. FOR MON., SEPT. 28
-- PCA-SURGERY-1-HNS, 9-25 -- Dr. David McLeod, 63, an Army
colonel, and chief of urology at Walter Reed Army Medical Center,
removed the cancerous prostates of former Sen. Bob Dole and retired
Gen. Norman Schwarzkopf, among other Washington notables. ``I knew
